{"source_key":"sha256-a153ef5d901086d9225a50321b8764ab","record_index":1271,"record_hash":"sha256:cf96e21d2723ffb2caf37e0d621015b62a233e8dc08022183265d323ae2bfd00","timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:21:43.218Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes. The destructive bit is here:\n\n[crates/gitbutler-oplog/src/oplog.rs:634](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/gitbutler-oplog/src/oplog.rs:634)\n\n`commit_snapshot()` reads `operations-log.toml`, then does:\n\n```rust\n.oplog_head()?\n.and_then(|head_id| repo.find_commit(head_id).ok());\n```\n\nIf `operations-log.toml` has a head but that commit can’t be found, it silently treats it as “no oplog”. Then it creates a brand-new root snapshot and overwrites the file here:\n\n[crates/gitbutler-oplog/src/state.rs:63](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/gitbutler-oplog/src/state.rs:63)\n\nThat behavior is even locked in by this test:\n\n[[REDACTED:entropy].rs:540]([REDACTED:entropy].rs:540)\n\n`head_corrupt_is_recreated_automatically` expects a corrupt oplog head to be reset. That’s probably the behavior users are seeing as “oplog overwritten”.\n\nThe setup path that triggers this is:\n\n[crates/gitbutler-branch-actions/src/actions.rs:53](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/gitbutler-branch-actions/src/actions.rs:53)\n\n`set_base_branch()` always tries to create a `SetBaseBranch` snapshot before doing the base branch operation. So if the app wrongly sends an already-configured project through setup again, it can touch the oplog even when the user is just re-confirming the same base branch.\n\nMy take: yes, we should make this non-destructive. Best minimal fix is two-part:\n\n1. Don’t create a `SetBaseBranch` snapshot when setting the already-configured target branch again.\n2. Stop silently re-rooting the oplog when `operations-log.toml` already contains a head that can’t be resolved. Return/log an error instead of overwriting the pointer.\n\nThat keeps real first-time setup working, but prevents an accidental setup flow from nuking oplog history.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-16T08:21:43.218Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}